# homeops-specific environment config.
# Copy or rename to .env, uncomment the keys below, then edit the values to
# match your setup. .env is gitignored; .env.example is tracked and serves
# as documentation.
#
# Vault-related keys are REQUIRED for the vault mirror to do anything. If
# they're absent or commented out, sync-to-vault.sh / sync-from-vault.sh
# print a configure-me message and no-op, and the session-start hook
# silently skips its vault delta check. Nothing breaks.
#
# Values are read literally (no shell expansion). Use absolute paths;
# $HOME and ~ are NOT expanded by the parser.
#
# Consumed by:
#   scripts/lib/vault-config.sh
#   scripts/homeops-session-start.sh
#   (and any script that sources scripts/lib/vault-config.sh)

# --- Obsidian vault mirror ---
# Where your Obsidian vault root lives on disk. The default in
# scripts/lib/vault-config.sh is a generic placeholder; override here to point
# at your actual vault. Typical values:
#
#   macOS iCloud-synced Obsidian:
#     /Users/youruser/Library/Mobile Documents/iCloud~md~obsidian/Documents/MyVault
#
#   Obsidian Sync (paid) or local-only vault:
#     /Users/youruser/Obsidian/MyVault
#
#   Syncthing vault:
#     /Users/youruser/SyncThing/Obsidian/MyVault

# HOMEOPS_VAULT_ROOT=/Users/youruser/Obsidian/MyVault

# Subpath under HOMEOPS_VAULT_ROOT where the sanitized repo mirror lives.
# Choose something that fits your vault's organizational scheme (JD numbers,
# topic folders, whatever).

# HOMEOPS_VAULT_MIRROR_SUBPATH=Tech/Homelab/homeops

# Subpath under HOMEOPS_VAULT_ROOT where raw (PII-OK) thinking lives.
# Claude reads here during the "abstract from vault" flow; never mirrored
# back as-is.

# HOMEOPS_VAULT_RAW_SUBPATH=Tech/Homelab/_raw

# --- Discipline audit staleness ---
# How many days since the last audit (or since conventions.md was created,
# if no audit on record yet) before homeops-session-start.sh warns. Default 90.

# AUDIT_STALENESS_DAYS=90
